{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "And one day somebody came running to me and said that somebody who I know from my hometown sent for me.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "She was in the third barrack, that they took a group of 30 people from a different camp, ready to be taken to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "I went there and this was a girl who I used to go to Sunday School with in junior high school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "She wasn't a close friend, but I knew her from junior high school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "And she came to me, and she hugged me, and she cried.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "She knew what her destiny is going to be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "But I guess she didn't know that her mother going to the left is not alive anymore when they arrived.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "So she asked me if I see her mother, if I survived to tell her mother what happened to her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "Of course, I felt horrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "These people were not sick.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "I mean, she really had-- there was nothing wrong with her except the same thing that was wrong with all of us, being undernourished and such.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 92,
      "text": "And I went to my cousin, and I asked her if there is anything we could do.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 93,
      "text": "It just so happened that there was a little girl who was in coma already, for a couple of days that Mengele didn't know about.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 94,
      "text": "Actually the day they were taken, she was dead already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 95,
      "text": "So the-- not my cousin, but another doctor who was sort of higher up in the administration of the hospital, a Polish lady, came with me.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 96,
      "text": "And I was standing behind this girl, and she came to this room where they were held.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 97,
      "text": "And she said, well, I'm going to check you out, all of you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 98,
      "text": "And she pointed at her, and said, come on, you'll be the first one.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
